div1.p: United States Circuit Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit

Columbia George, Appellant
vs.
Charles B. Hopkins, United States Marshal for the Western District of Washington, et al., Appellees
Certified Copy of Decree of Dismissal
Filed in the U.S. Circuit Court, OCT 25 1906. A. Reeves Ayres, Clerk.
United States Circuit Court of Appeals For the Ninth Circuit.

Columbia George,
vs.
Charles B. Hopkins, United States Marshal for the Western District of Washington, and the United States of America. Appellees.
Appeal form the United States Circuit Court for the Western District of Washington, Northern Division.

This cause came on to be heard upon the motion of the counsel fo rthe appelles to dismiss the appeal therein agreeably to the provisions of subdivision one (1) of rule sixteen (16) of the rules of practice of this Court. And it appearing to the Court that the appellant has failed to file the record thereof and docket the case by or before the return day, and has failed to comply with the said rule, and that agreeably to the said rule, the appelle has docketed the case and produced and filed a certificate of the clerk of the Court below stating the case and certifying that the above-entitled cause was duly led to this Court:

In consideration whereof, and agreeably to the provisions of subdivision one (1) of rule sixteen (16) of the rules of practice of this Court, it is ordered, adjudged and decreed by this Court that the appeal in this cause be, and hereby is dismissed.
